TRAYER-SRG(1)                                                    TRAYER-SRG(1)



NNAAMMEE
         trayer-srg - a lightweight GTK2-based systray for UNIX desktop

SSYYNNOOPPSSYYSS
       ttrraayyeerr [[ _O_P_T_I_O_N_S ]]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       trayer  is  small  program  designed  to  provide systray functionality
       present in GNOME/KDE desktop  enviroments  for  window  managers  which
       doesn't  support that function. It's similar to other applications such
       as 'peksystray' and 'docker'.

       trayer code was extracted from fbpanel application, you can  find  more
       about it on it's homepage: _h_t_t_p_:_/_/_f_b_p_a_n_e_l_._s_o_u_r_c_e_f_o_r_g_e_._n_e_t_/

       You can find new versions of trayer and support on FVWM-Crystal project
       homepage: _h_t_t_p_:_/_/_f_v_w_m_-_c_r_y_s_t_a_l_._b_e_r_l_i_o_s_._d_e_/

       There is also a debian maintained version of trayer, you can  find  the
       mercurial repository on: _h_t_t_p_:_/_/_h_g_._d_e_b_i_a_n_._o_r_g_/_h_g_/_c_o_l_l_a_b_-_m_a_i_n_t_/_t_r_a_y_e_r

       trayer-srg  was  forked  from  trayer in january 2010 to add some fancy
       features and clean up code.  It contains all changes  from  above  ver-
       sions  as  far  as  known.   Code of trayer-srg can be found on github:
       _h_t_t_p_:_/_/_g_i_t_h_u_b_._c_o_m_/_s_a_r_g_o_n_/_t_r_a_y_e_r_-_s_r_g

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh     prints help message and exits

       --vv     prints version and exits

       ----eeddggee EDGE
              Use _E_D_G_E for orientation. Possible values  for  _E_D_G_E  are  lleefftt,,
              rriigghhtt,, ttoopp,, bboottttoomm or nnoonnee..  The default value is bboottttoomm..

       ----aalliiggnn ALIGNMENT
              Orientation  of  docked  icons inside the trayer panel. Possible
              values are lleefftt,, cceenntteerr,, rriigghhtt,, or nnoonnee..  The default  value  is
              cceenntteerr..

       ----mmaarrggiinn NUM
              Length of margin in pixels. The default value is 00..

       ----ddiissttaannccee NUM
              Space  between  trayer's  window and screen edge.  When set to 0
              the option has no effect.  The default value is 00..

       ----ddiissttaanncceeffrroomm EDGE
              Specifies which edge to calculate  distance  from,  see  ----eeddggee..
              The default value is ttoopp..
               When ----ddiissttaannccee is 0 then this option has no effect.

       ----wwiiddtthhttyyppee TYPE
              Determine  how width is calculated. Possible values for _T_Y_P_E are
              ppiixxeell,, ppeerrcceenntt,, rreeqquueesstt or nnoonnee..  The default value is ppeerrcceenntt..

       ----wwiiddtthh NUM
              Width of a panel. When ----wwiiddtthhttyyppee==rreeqquueesstt this  option  has  no
              effect. The default value is 110000..

       ----hheeiigghhttttyyppee TYPE
              Determine how height is calculated. Possible values for _T_Y_P_E are
              ppiixxeell,, rreeqquueesstt or nnoonnee..

              The default value is ppiixxeell..

       ----hheeiigghhtt NUM
              Height of a panel. When ----hheeiiggtthhttyyppee==rreeqquueesstt this option has  no
              effect. The default value is 2266..

       ----SSeettDDoocckkTTppee BOOL
              Identify panel window type as dock. The default value is ttrruuee..

       ----SSeettPPaarrttiiaallSSttrruutt BOOL
              Reserve  panel's  space  so that it will not be covered by maxi-
              mazied windows. The default value is ffaallssee..

       ----ttrraannssppaarreenntt BOOL
              Use transparency. Default value is ffaallssee..

       ----ttiinntt NUM
              Color used to "tint" background wallpaper with.   _N_U_M  is  32bit
              width hexadecimal number.  The default value is 00xxFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF..

       ----aallpphhaa NUM
              Percentage of transparency.  _N_U_M should be a value between 0 and
              256. The default value is 112277..

       ----eexxppaanndd BOOL
              Specifies  if  trayer  can  accomodate  extra   space   or   not
              <true|false>. The default value is ttrruuee..

       ----ppaaddddiinngg NUM
              Number  of  extra  pixel space between trayer's window frame and
              docked icons. The default value is 00..

       ----mmoonniittoorr NUM|STRING
              Define the monitor on which you like trayer to appear, number of
              zero  to  number  of monitors minus one, or the string "primary"
              are valid. The default value is 00..

EEXXAAMMPPLLEESS
       Place trayer to the top right edge of  the  screen  and  prevent  other
       fullsize windows to overlay it:
              trayer trayer --edge top --align right --SetDockType true --SetPartialStrut true --expand true --transparent true

BBUUGGSS
       Report  bugs  to  the  issue tracker: _h_t_t_p_s_:_/_/_g_i_t_h_u_b_._c_o_m_/_s_a_r_g_o_n_/_t_r_a_y_e_r_-
       _s_r_g_/_i_s_s_u_e_s

